grumpybozo/116926550702909383', 'source_type': "['']", 'source_level': 2, 'text': [], 'observables': {}}, {'title': 'CVE-2026-1609 - Org.keycloak/keycloak-quarkus-server: keycloak: unauthorized access via jwt authorization grant with disabled users', 'publication_date': 'Thu, 16 Jul 2026 01:16:30 +0000', 'source': 'https://cvefeed.io/vuln/detail/CVE-2026-1609', 'source_type': "['']", 'source_level': 2, 'text': ['A flaw was found in Keycloak. When the JSON Web Token (JWT) authorization grant preview feature is enabled and a user account is disabled, Keycloak fails to validate the user’s disabled status during JWT authorization grant processing. A remote attacker with low privileges can exploit this improper access control vulnerability by presenting a valid assertion token from an external identity provider to obtain a JWT for a disabled user. This allows unauthorized access to sensitive resources.', 'The following products are affected byCVE-2026-1609vulnerability. Even ifcvefeed.iois aware of the exact versions of the products that are affected, the information is not represented in the table below.', 'Common Attack Pattern Enumeration and Classification (CAPEC) stores attack patterns, which are descriptions of the common attributes and approaches employed by adversaries to exploit theCVE-2026-1609weaknesses.', 'We scan GitHub repositories to detect new proof-of-concept exploits. Following list is a collection of public exploits and proof-of-concepts, which have been published on GitHub (sorted by the most recently updated).', "Vulnerability history details can be useful for understanding the evolution of a vulnerability, and for identifying the most recent changes that may impact the vulnerability's severity, exploitability, or other characteristics."], 'observables': {'domain-name': ['cvefeed.io'], 'email-addr': ['secalert@redhat.com'], 'url': ['https://access.redhat.com/jbossnetwork/restricted/listSoftware.html', 'https://access.redhat.com/security/cve/CVE-2026-1609', 'https://bugzilla.redhat.com/show_bug.cgi?id=2435257', 'https://github.com/keycloak/keycloak/issues/46144', 'https://github.com/keycloak/keycloak/releases/tag/26.5.3'], 'vulnerability': ['CVE-2026-1609']}}, {'title': 'CVE-2026-55652 - Wekan: Header-login IP allowlist bypass via X-Forwarded-For spoofing in Wekan allows unauthenticated full account takeover (incl. admin)', 'publication_date': 'Wed, 15 Jul 2026 22:17:26 +0000', 'source': 'https://cvefeed.io/vuln/detail/CVE-2026-55652', 'source_type': "['']", 'source_level': 2, 'text': ['Wekan is open source kanban built with Meteor. Prior to 9.46, header-login with HEADER_LOGIN_TRUSTED_IPS uses getRequestIp() in server/lib/headerLoginAuth.js to trust the client-supplied X-Forwarded-For header before the real socket address, allowing an unauthenticated attacker to send HEADER_LOGIN_ID for any username and receive a meteor_login_token session, including for admin. This issue is fixed in version 9.46.', 'The following products are affected byCVE-2026-55652vulnerability. Even ifcvefeed.iois aware of the exact versions of the products that are affected, the information is not represented in the table below.', 'Common Attack Pattern Enumeration and Classification (CAPEC) stores attack patterns, which are descriptions of the common attributes and approaches employed by adversaries to exploit theCVE-2026-55652weaknesses.', 'We scan GitHub repositories to detect new proof-of-concept exploits. Following list is a collection of public exploits and proof-of-concepts, which have been published on GitHub (sorted by the most recently updated).', "Vulnerability history details can be useful for understanding the evolution of a vulnerability, and for identifying the most recent changes that may impact the vulnerability's severity, exploitability, or other characteristics."], 'observables': {'email-addr': ['hey@cvefeed.io', 'security-advisories@github.com'], 'file': [{'hash_type': 'SHA-1', 'values': ['b181889a565254bc9bf79379a34fc7f617ccda28']}], 'url': ['https://github.com/wekan/wekan/commit/b181889a565254bc9bf79379a34fc7f617ccda28', 'https://github.com/wekan/wekan/releases/tag/v9.46', 'https://github.com/wekan/wekan/security/advisories/GHSA-jggc-qvfc-jr6x'], 'vulnerability': ['CVE-2026-55652', 'GHSA-JGGC-QVFC-JR6X']}}, {'title': 'CVE-2026-55576 - MaaAssistantArknights: PR-title expression injection in release-preparation.yml', 'publication_date': 'Wed, 15 Jul 2026 22:17:26 +0000', 'source': 'https://cvefeed.io/vuln/detail/CVE-2026-55576', 'source_type': "['']", 'source_level': 2, 'text': ['MaaAssistantArknights is a one-click tool for daily Arknights tasks. In the current dev-v2 workflow, .github/workflows/release-preparation.yml inlined attacker-controlled github.event.pull_request.title into a run: shell command during the pull_request opened, reopened, and ready_for_review events, so a non-draft fork PR whose title starts with Release v could execute shell commands on the ubuntu-latest runner during the generate-changelog job. This vulnerability is fixed by commit cafc3946059e6337d2089d4fec8b6885ba17c332.', 'The following products are affected byCVE-2026-55576vulnerability. Even ifcvefeed.iois aware of the exact versions of the products that are affected, the information is not represented in the table below.', 'Common Attack Pattern Enumeration and Classification (CAPEC) stores attack patterns, which are descriptions of the common attributes and approaches employed by adversaries to exploit theCVE-2026-55576weaknesses.', 'We scan GitHub repositories to detect new proof-of-concept exploits. Following list is a collection of public exploits and proof-of-concepts, which have been published on GitHub (sorted by the most recently updated).', "Vulnerability history details can be useful for understanding the evolution of a vulnerability, and for identifying the most recent changes that may impact the vulnerability's severity, exploitability, or other characteristics."], 'observables': {'domain-name': ['cvefeed.io'], 'email-addr': ['security-advisories@github.com'], 'file': [{'hash_type': 'SHA-1', 'values': ['cafc3946059e6337d2089d4fec8b6885ba17c332']}], 'url': ['https://github.com/MaaAssistantArknights/MaaAssistantArknights/commit/cafc3946059e6337d2089d4fec8b6885ba17c332', 'https://github.com/MaaAssistantArknights/MaaAssistantArknights/security/advisories/GHSA-pqx2-5g66-f5w8'], 'vulnerability': ['CVE-2026-55576', 'GHSA-PQX2-5G66-F5W8']}}, {'title': 'CVE-2026-55445 - Qinglong: Incomplete fix for CVE-2026-3965: Improper Authentication', 'publication_date': 'Wed, 15 Jul 2026 22:17:26 +0000', 'source': 'https://cvefeed.io/vuln/detail/CVE-2026-55445', 'source_type': "['']", 'source_level': 2, 'text': ["Qinglong is a timed task management platform supporting Python3, JavaScript, Shell, and Typescript. Prior to 2.20.1, the init guard middleware in back/loaders/express.ts checks /api/user/init but not /open/user/init, while rewrite('/open/*', '/api/$1') rewrites the whitelisted /open/* path after JWT authentication and the guard have passed; an unauthenticated attacker can send PUT /open/user/init to reset administrator credentials on an initialized instance. This issue is fixed in 2.20.1.", 'The following products are affected byCVE-2026-55445vulnerability. Even ifcvefeed.iois aware of the exact versions of the products that are affected, the information is not represented in the table below.', 'Common Attack Pattern Enumeration and Classification (CAPEC) stores attack patterns, which are descriptions of the common attributes and approaches employed by adversaries to exploit theCVE-2026-55445weaknesses.', 'We scan GitHub repositories to detect new proof-of-concept exploits. Following list is a collection of public exploits and proof-of-concepts, which have been published on GitHub (sorted by the most recently updated).', "Vulnerability history details can be useful for understanding the evolution of a vulnerability, and for identifying the most recent changes that may impact the vulnerability's severity, exploitability, or other characteristics."], 'observables': {'domain-name': ['cvefeed.io'], 'email-addr': ['security-advisories@github.com'], 'file': [{'hash_type': 'SHA-1', 'values': ['6bec52dca158481258315ba0fc2f11206df7b719']}], 'url': ['https://github.com/whyour/qinglong/commit/6bec52dca158481258315ba0fc2f11206df7b719', 'https://github.com/whyour/qinglong/pull/2941', 'https://github.com/whyour/qinglong/security/advisories/GHSA-v667-gc2r-2xm7'], 'vulnerability': ['CVE-2026-55445', 'CVE-2026-3965', 'GHSA-V667-GC2R-2XM7']}}, {'title': 'CVE-2026-55234 - Wekan: Broken access control: any authenticated user can move their Cards/Lists/Swimlanes into a private board they are not a member of (cross-board write via collection allow rule)', 'publication_date': 'Wed, 15 Jul 2026 22:17:25 +0000', 'source': 'https://cvefeed.io/vuln/detail/CVE-2026-55234', 'source_type': "['']", 'source_level': 2, 'text': ['Wekan is open source kanban built with Meteor. Prior to 9.37, Wekan DDP update allow rules in server/permissions/cards.js, server/permissions/lists.js, and server/permissions/swimlanes.js authorize against the stored source boardId and do not validate a new boardId in the update modifier. Any authenticated user with write access to their own board can call /cards/update, /lists/update, or /swimlanes/update to move cards, lists, or swimlanes into a private board they are not a member of. This issue is fixed in version 9.37.', 'The following products are affected byCVE-2026-55234vulnerability. Even ifcvefeed.iois aware of the exact versions of the products that are affected, the information is not represented in the table below.', 'Common Attack Pattern Enumeration and Classification (CAPEC) stores attack patterns, which are descriptions of the common attributes and approaches employed by adversaries to exploit theCVE-2026-55234weaknesses.', 'We scan GitHub repositories to detect new proof-of-concept exploits. Following list is a collection of public exploits and proof-of-concepts, which have been published on GitHub (sorted by the most recently updated).', "Vulnerability history details can be useful for understanding the evolution of a vulnerability, and for identifying the most recent changes that may impact the vulnerability's severity, exploitability, or other characteristics."], 'observables': {'domain-name': ['cvefeed.io'], 'email-addr': ['security-advisories@github.com'], 'file': [{'hash_type': 'SHA-1', 'values': ['d369a3614a4737c29d48a6345a790edf2506ddae']}], 'url': ['https://github.com/wekan/wekan/commit/d369a3614a4737c29d48a6345a790edf2506ddae', 'https://github.com/wekan/wekan/releases/tag/v9.37', 'https://github.com/wekan/wekan/security/advisories/GHSA-gm7v-pc38-53jr'], 'vulnerability': ['CVE-2026-55234', 'GHSA-GM7V-PC38-53JR']}}, {'title': 'CVE-2026-54458 - AVideo: Unauthenticated Stored DOM Cross-Site Scripting via Per-Client Metadata Broadcast in YPTSocket Plugin', 'publication_date': 'Wed, 15 Jul 2026 22:17:19 +0000', 'source': 'https://cvefeed.io/vuln/detail/CVE-2026-54458', 'source_type': "['']", 'source_level': 2, 'text': ["WWBN AVideo is an open source video platform. Versions prior to 29.0 contain a stored DOM Cross-Site Scripting vulnerability in the YPTSocket plugin. Any unauthenticated remote attacker can execute arbitrary JavaScript in the authenticated origin of every administrator currently viewing a page that renders the YPTSocket online-users debug panel. plugin/YPTSocket/getWebSocket.json.php issues a signed WebSocket token to any anonymous caller, and MessageSQLiteV2::onOpen at plugin/YPTSocket/MessageSQLiteV2.php lines 91 and 110 reads the attacker-controlled webSocketSelfURI and page_title query parameters from the WebSocket connection URL with no validation. Both values persist into the in-memory SQLite connections table and broadcast inside the users_id_online array sent to every connected client; on the client, plugin/YPTSocket/script.js::updateSocketUserCard interpolates the broadcast page_title into an HTML template literal that is passed to jQuery $.append(html), which parses attacker bytes into live DOM nodes including  with inline event handlers. Successful attackers can can read non-HttpOnly cookies and the CSRF token rendered into the admin dashboard, issue authenticated requests to any admin-only endpoint, exfiltrate the admin dashboard DOM, and chain into any admin-context mutation. When the victim is an AVideo administrator, the attacker turns a single anonymous WebSocket connection into full administrative takeover via the admin's own session. This issue has been patched by https://github.com/WWBN/AVideo/commit/8be71e53ccbe9b84b30870db386fb4d2b11e1c16.", 'The following products are affected byCVE-2026-54458vulnerability. Even ifcvefeed.iois aware of the exact versions of the products that are affected, the information is not represented in the table below.', 'Common Attack Pattern Enumeration and Classification (CAPEC) stores attack patterns, which are descriptions of the common attributes and approaches employed by adversaries to exploit theCVE-2026-54458weaknesses.', 'We scan GitHub repositories to detect new proof-of-concept exploits. Following list is a collection of public exploits and proof-of-concepts, which have been published on GitHub (sorted by the most recently updated).', "Vulnerability history details can be useful for understanding the evolution of a vulnerability, and for identifying the most recent changes that may impact the vulnerability's severity, exploitability, or other characteristics."], 'observables': {'domain-name': ['cvefeed.io'], 'email-addr': ['security-advisories@github.com'], 'file': [{'hash_type': 'SHA-1', 'values': ['8be71e53ccbe9b84b30870db386fb4d2b11e1c16']}], 'url': ['https://github.com/WWBN/AVideo/commit/8be71e53ccbe9b84b30870db386fb4d2b11e1c16', 'https://github.com/WWBN/AVideo/security/advisories/GHSA-8whc-2wmv-ww35'], 'vulnerability': ['CVE-2026-54458', 'GHSA-8WHC-2WMV-WW35']}}, {'title': 'CVE-2026-52893 - Wekan: OIDC Account Takeover via Unconditional Email-Based Account Merge in onCreateUser hook', 'publication_date': 'Wed, 15 Jul 2026 22:17:16 +0000', 'source': 'https://cvefeed.io/vuln/detail/CVE-2026-52893', 'source_type': "['']", 'source_level': 2, 'text': ["Wekan is open source kanban built with Meteor. Prior to 9.32, the Wekan Accounts.onCreateUser hook in server/models/users.js merges OIDC logins into existing accounts when the OIDC email or username matches an existing Wekan user, without verifying ownership or checking email_verified. An attacker using an OIDC provider account with a victim's email or username can cause Wekan to merge the attacker's OIDC credentials into the victim account and then log in as that account. This issue is fixed in version 9.32.", 'The following products are affected byCVE-2026-52893vulnerability. Even ifcvefeed.iois aware of the exact versions of the products that are affected, the information is not represented in the table below.', 'Common Attack Pattern Enumeration and Classification (CAPEC) stores attack patterns, which are descriptions of the common attributes and approaches employed by adversaries to exploit theCVE-2026-52893weaknesses.', 'We scan GitHub repositories to detect new proof-of-concept exploits. Following list is a collection of public exploits and proof-of-concepts, which have been published on GitHub (sorted by the most recently updated).', "Vulnerability history details can be useful for understanding the evolution of a vulnerability, and for identifying the most recent changes that may impact the vulnerability's severity, exploitability, or other characteristics."], 'observables': {'domain-name': ['cvefeed.io'], 'email-addr': ['security-advisories@github.com'], 'file': [{'hash_type': 'SHA-1', 'values': ['73204d4e0a7d77a1b186b3d76e8eaf2f3e7c9fd9']}], 'url': ['https://github.com/wekan/wekan/commit/73204d4e0a7d77a1b186b3d76e8eaf2f3e7c9fd9', 'https://github.com/wekan/wekan/releases/tag/v9.32', 'https://github.com/wekan/wekan/security/advisories/GHSA-mp7g-hj5q-gxhq'], 'vulnerability': ['CVE-2026-52893', 'GHSA-MP7G-HJ5Q-GXHQ']}}, {'title': 'ZDI-26-444: 7-Zip XZ Decompression Heap-based Buffer Overflow Remote Code Execution Vulnerability', 'publication_date': 'Wed, 15 Jul 2026 00:00:00 -0500', 'source': 'http://www.zerodayinitiative.com/advisories/ZDI-26-444/', 'source_type': "['']", 'source_level': 2, 'text': ['This vulnerability allows remote attackers to execute arbitrary code on affected installations of 7-Zip. User interaction is required to exploit this vulnerability in that the target must visit a malicious page or open a malicious file.', 'The specific flaw exists within the processing of XZ chunked data. Crafted XZ-compressed data can trigger an overflow of a heap-based buffer. An attacker can leverage this vulnerability to execute code in the context of the current process.'], 'observables': {'vulnerability': ['CVE-2026-14266']}}, {'title': 'ZDI-26-443: Linux Kernel vmwgfx Integer Overflow Local Privilege Escalation Vulnerability', 'publication_date': 'Wed, 15 Jul 2026 00:00:00 -0500', 'source': 'http://www.zerodayinitiative.com/advisories/ZDI-26-443/', 'source_type': "['']", 'source_level': 2, 'text': ['This vulnerability allows local attackers to escalate privileges on affected installations of Linux Kernel. An attacker must first obtain the ability to execute low-privileged code on the target system in order to exploit this vulnerability.', 'The specific flaw exists within the handling of surface allocations. The issue results from the lack of proper validation of user-supplied data, which can result in an integer overflow before allocating a buffer. An attacker can leverage this vulnerability to escalate privileges and execute arbitrary code in the context of the kernel.'], 'observables': {'email-addr': ['20260623193314.506257-1-ian.forbes@broadcom.com'], 'url': ['https://lore.kernel.org/dri-devel/20260623193314.506257-1-ian.forbes@broadcom.com/T/#u']}}, {'title': 'ZDI-26-442: Linux Kernel CAN ISO-TP Protocol Race Condition Local Privilege Escalation Vulnerability', 'publication_date': 'Wed, 15 Jul 2026 00:00:00 -0500', 'source': 'http://www.zerodayinitiative.com/advisories/ZDI-26-442/', 'source_type': "['']", 'source_level': 2, 'text': ['This vulnerability allows local attackers to escalate privileges on affected installations of Linux Kernel. An attacker must first obtain the ability to execute low-privileged code on the target system in order to exploit this vulnerability.', 'The specific flaw exists within the handling of socket close. The issue results from the lack of proper locking when performing operations on an object. An attacker can leverage this vulnerability to escalate privileges and execute arbitrary code in the context of the kernel.'], 'observables': {'email-addr': ['20260707083228.47629-1-socketcan@hartkopp.net'], 'url': ['https://lore.kernel.org/linux-can/20260707083228.47629-1-socketcan@hartkopp.net/']}}, {'title': 'ZDI-26-441: dnsmasq DNS Response Heap-based Buffer Overflow Remote Code Execution Vulnerability', 'publication_date': 'Wed, 15 Jul 2026 00:00:00 -0500', 'source': 'http://www.zerodayinitiative.com/advisories/ZDI-26-441/', 'source_type': "['']", 'source_level': 2, 'text': ['The specific flaw exists within the parsing of CNAME records. The issue results from the lack of proper validation of the length of user-supplied data prior to copying it to a heap-based buffer. An attacker can leverage this vulnerability to execute code in the context of the service.'], 'observables': {'domain-name': ['dnsmasq.org'], 'vulnerability': ['CVE-2026-2291']}}, {'title': 'ZDI-26-440: Fuji Electric Tellus pcid64 Driver Untrusted Pointer Dereference Denial of Service Vulnerability', 'publication_date': 'Wed, 15 Jul 2026 00:00:00 -0500', 'source': 'http://www.zerodayinitiative.com/advisories/ZDI-26-440/', 'source_type': "['']", 'source_level': 2, 'text': ['This vulnerability allows local attackers to create a denial-of-service condition on affected installations of Fuji Electric Tellus. An attacker must first obtain the ability to execute low-privileged code on the target system in order to exploit this vulnerability.', 'The specific flaw exists within calls to methods in the pcid64 driver. The issue results from the lack of proper validation of a user-supplied value prior to dereferencing it as a pointer. An attacker can leverage this vulnerability to create a denial-of-service condition on the system.'], 'observables': {'domain-name': ['cisa.gov'], 'url': ['http://www.cisa.gov/news-events/ics-advisories/icsa-26-132-01', 'https://www.cisa.gov/news-events/ics-advisories/icsa-26-132-01'], 'vulnerability': ['CVE-2026-8108']}}, {'title': 'ZDI-26-439: Fuji Electric Tellus pcid64 Driver Exposed Dangerous Method Local Privilege Escalation Vulnerability', 'publication_date': 'Wed, 15 Jul 2026 00:00:00 -0500', 'source': 'http://www.zerodayinitiative.com/advisories/ZDI-26-439/', 'source_type': "['']", 'source_level': 2, 'text': ['This vulnerability allows local attackers to escalate privileges on affected installations of Fuji Electric Tellus. An attacker must first obtain the ability to execute low-privileged code on the target system in order to exploit this vulnerability.', 'The specific flaw exists within calls to methods in the pcid64 driver. The issue results from exposed dangerous functions. An attacker can leverage this vulnerability to escalate privileges and execute arbitrary code in the context of SYSTEM.'], 'observables': {'domain-name': ['cisa.gov'], 'url': ['http://www.cisa.gov/news-events/ics-advisories/icsa-26-132-01', 'https://www.cisa.gov/news-events/ics-advisories/icsa-26-132-01'], 'vulnerability': ['CVE-2026-8108']}}, {'title': 'ZDI-26-438: Rockwell Automation Arena Simulation DOE File Parsing Out-Of-Bounds Write Remote Code Execution Vulnerability', 'publication_date': 'Wed, 15 Jul 2026 00:00:00 -0500', 'source': 'http://www.zerodayinitiative.com/advisories/ZDI-26-438/', 'source_type': "['']", 'source_level': 2, 'text': ['This vulnerability allows remote attackers to execute arbitrary code on affected installations of Rockwell Automation Arena Simulation. User interaction is required to exploit this vulnerability in that the target must visit a malicious page or open a malicious file.', 'The specific flaw exists within the parsing of DOE files. The issue results from the lack of proper validation of user-supplied data, which can result in a write past the end of an allocated object. An attacker can leverage this vulnerability to execute code in the context of the current process.'], 'observables': {'domain-name': ['cisa.gov'], 'url': ['http://www.cisa.gov/news-events/ics-advisories/icsa-24-345-06', 'https://www.cisa.gov/news-events/ics-advisories/icsa-24-345-06'], 'vulnerability': ['CVE-2026-6071']}}, {'title': 'Multiples vulnérabilités dans Microsoft Edge (15 juillet 2026)', 'publication_date': 'Wed, 15 Jul 2026 00:00:00 +0000', 'source': 'https://www.cert.ssi.gouv.fr/avis/CERTFR-2026-AVI-0867/', 'source_type': "['operational', 'vulnerabilities']", 'source_level': 1, 'text': ["De multiples vulnérabilités ont été découvertes dans Microsoft Edge. Elles permettent à un attaquant de provoquer une exécution de code arbitraire à distance, une élévation de privilèges et un problème de sécurité non spécifié par l'éditeur."], 'observables': {'vulnerability': ['CVE-2026-14090', 'CVE-2026-13777', 'CVE-2026-13778', 'CVE-2026-13785', 'CVE-2026-13788', 'CVE-2026-13791', 'CVE-2026-13792', 'CVE-2026-13795', 'CVE-2026-13805', 'CVE-2026-13807', 'CVE-2026-13808', 'CVE-2026-13809', 'CVE-2026-13812', 'CVE-2026-13813', 'CVE-2026-13816', 'CVE-2026-13819', 'CVE-2026-13822', 'CVE-2026-13825', 'CVE-2026-13826', 'CVE-2026-13827', 'CVE-2026-13833', 'CVE-2026-13842', 'CVE-2026-13843', 'CVE-2026-13846', 'CVE-2026-13847', 'CVE-2026-13850', 'CVE-2026-13851', 'CVE-2026-13852', 'CVE-2026-13856', 'CVE-2026-13862'